| 249 | D | A method paper (also called an application paper) describes a novel technique or procedure. |
| 250 | A | CDS has shown benefits in diagnosis, treatment guidelines, clinical pathway adherence. |
| 251 | C | An outcome measure describes a real-world patient benefit. Using an appropriate drug-drug interaction checker, maintaining an accurate active medication list would be expected to reduce the number of drug-drug interactions. |
| 252 | A | A milestone is a zero-length task meant to signify completion of some part of a project. |
| 253 | D | Distributive bargaining is encountered when there is a fixed amount of resources that must be split among all parties, such as when buyer and seller haggle over a price. |
| 254 | D | Real time communication, such as interactive video, is a form of synchronous communication. |
| 255 | A | Sensitivity. Sensitivity is the probability of a test giving a true positive if we know a patient has a disease. |
| 256 | D | This represents a finish-to-finish dependency. Task B can not be finished until task A is finished. |
| 257 | A | Data stewardship includes many processes, including those that ensure that the right data is stored in the right place in the database so that users can get to it easily. |
| 258 | A | ICD-10 supplanted ICD-9 as the most commonly used method of encoding diagnoses in 2016. |
| 259 | D | Telepresence, which is the simulation of a remote environment, requires immediate feedback to be successful. |
| 260 | C | User centered design should consider user goals, motivations, and environment throughout the design and development phases. |
